# Security Rules

## Authentication (JWT)

- JWT tokens validated in `JwtAuthFilter` on every protected request
- Token signing uses a secret from environment variables, never hard-coded
- Set short token expiry (15-30 min access, 7 day refresh)
- Refresh tokens stored securely; revoke on logout
- Never log JWT tokens or include them in error responses

## Authorization

- Use method-level security with `@PreAuthorize("hasRole('ROLE_X')")` on service methods
- Controllers should not contain authorization logic
- Validate resource ownership: users can only access their own data
- Admin endpoints must require `ROLE_ADMIN`

## Input Validation

- Validate all request bodies with `@Valid` + Bean Validation annotations
- Sanitize user input to prevent XSS (escape HTML in text fields)
- Use parameterized queries exclusively; never concatenate user input into SQL
- Validate file uploads: check MIME type, enforce size limits, scan content
- Reject unexpected fields in API requests (use `@JsonIgnoreProperties(ignoreUnknown = false)`)

## Data Protection

- Hash passwords with BCrypt (`BCryptPasswordEncoder`); never store plain text
- Never return passwords, tokens, or secrets in API responses
- Mask sensitive data in logs (email, phone, financial amounts)
- Use HTTPS in production; reject HTTP connections
- Encrypt sensitive data at rest where required

## Error Handling

- Never expose stack traces, SQL errors, or internal paths to clients
- Return generic error messages for 500 errors: "An internal error occurred"
- Log full error details server-side with correlation IDs
- Use standardized error response format with error code, message, and timestamp

## CORS

- Configure allowed origins explicitly in `CorsConfig`; no wildcard (`*`) in production
- Restrict allowed methods to those actually used (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Set `allowCredentials: true` only when needed for cookie/auth header flows

## API Security

- Rate limit public endpoints (login, registration, password reset)
- Implement CSRF protection for cookie-based auth flows
- Set security headers: `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`
- Disable Spring Boot Actuator endpoints in production or protect with authentication

## Frontend Security

- Store JWT in memory or httpOnly cookies; never in localStorage
- Sanitize any user-generated content before rendering (prevent XSS)
- Validate redirect URLs to prevent open redirect attacks
- Do not expose API keys or secrets in frontend code or environment files committed to git
